SIMPLE: intolerable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intolerable
<hw>In*tol"er*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>intol⟦eacute⟧rable</ets>, L. <ets>intolerabilis</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Tolerable</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not tolerable; not capable of being borne or
endured; not proper or right to be allowed; insufferable; insupportable;
unbearable; <as>as, <ex>intolerable</ex> pain; <ex>intolerable</ex> heat
or cold; an <ex>intolerable</ex> burden.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 782 --></p>

<p><q>His insolence is more <qex>intolerable</qex>⟦br⟧
Than all the princes in the land beside.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Enormous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This <qex>intolerable</qex> deal of sack.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>In*tol"er*a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>In*tol"er*a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intolerance</ent>⟦br⟧
